transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi.

Speaker 2: Thank you for calling Niagara.

Speaker 1: How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: How are you today?

Speaker 1: Good, and yourself?

Speaker 2: OK.

Speaker 1: I placed an order yesterday.

Speaker 2: And when I received my final total for everything,

Speaker 1: that was fine.

Speaker 2: But there was also a notation for an automatic refill.

Speaker 1: I do not want an automatic refill.

Speaker 2: OK.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so we give you, this is a prescription.

Speaker 2: So we give you a whole month for you to be able to try it

Speaker 1: and see how you like it.

Speaker 2: And you're always able to modify also your monthly interval

Speaker 1: to your preference.

Speaker 2: So usually a quantity of 10 is good for a month.

Speaker 1: However, you can always go ahead and adjust it

Speaker 2: to every two months or every three months.

Speaker 1: But we do give you a whole month in the beginning

Speaker 2: for you to be able to try it and see how you want to move forward,

Speaker 1: whether you end up keeping it.

Speaker 2: OK, I'm going to tell you right now, I do not

Speaker 1: want an automatic refill.

Speaker 2: If I decide to buy more, I will order more.

Speaker 1: OK, so like I said, we do give you a whole month for you

Speaker 2: to try it.

Speaker 1: So I want you to cancel the automatic refill right now.

Speaker 2: So that would be canceling the order

Speaker 1: and you wouldn't receive anything.

Speaker 2: Because it's a prescription.

Speaker 1: Why is that?

Speaker 2: We pay for that prescription, not the customer.

Speaker 1: This is a prescription of over $300 that we paid for.

Speaker 2: This is a prescription that gets approved by a doctor,

Speaker 1: a certified physician.

Speaker 2: So when do I cancel?

Speaker 1: That's what I said.

Speaker 2: Once you receive it, once you receive your order,

Speaker 1: you have a whole month to try it and see

Speaker 2: whether you want to continue keeping it, ordering it,

Speaker 1: or whether you want to cancel the prescription, which

Speaker 2: for most of the part, our customers

Speaker 1: love to keep the prescription because they

Speaker 2: love how the pill works.

Speaker 1: So what is my status right now?

Speaker 2: So right now, you are a customer of ours.

Speaker 1: You placed this order.

Speaker 2: So like I said, you have a whole month to try it.

Speaker 1: And if you want to make any changes,

Speaker 2: you just have to give us a call before February 25th.

Speaker 1: Before when?

Speaker 2: February 25th.

Speaker 1: Yes, you got it.

Speaker 2: OK, thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Give me a minute.

Speaker 2: February 25th, you said?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: You call this number?

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: Call this number.

Speaker 1: And at that point in time, I can cancel?

Speaker 2: Yeah, you can cancel or you can decide

Speaker 1: to keep your prescription as is.

Speaker 2: Or you can adjust the monthly interval to your preference.

Speaker 1: OK, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Bye.
